<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of 
your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Author&#8217;s Names. &#34;Title of Article.&#34; <em>Title of Publication</em> 
	volume.number (date of publication): page numbers. <em>Name of Database</em>. 
	Medium of publication. Date of access.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span title="Author&#8217;s Names">Smith, Alex, and Beryl Brown</span>. 
	&#34;<span title="Title of Article">Glamorizing Domesticity: Narratives of Marriage and Motherhood in Desperate Housewives</span>.&#34; 
	<em><span title="Title of Publication">Media Studies</span></em> 
	<span title="volume.number">46.3</span> 
	(<span title="date of publication">Mar. 2056</span>): 
	<span title="page numbers">110&#45;23</span>. 
	<em><span title="Name of Database">Expanded Academic</span></em>. 
	<span title="Medium of publication">Web</span>. 
	<span title="Date of access">23 Oct. 2057</span>.
</blockquote>
